<h2>Summary</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Use Node.js built-in <code>crypto.createHash()</code> for all non-password hashing — no dependencies needed</li>
  <li>SHA-256 is the safe default for general-purpose cryptographic hashing</li>
  <li>MD5 is acceptable for checksums and cache keys, never for security</li>
  <li>Always use bcrypt, scrypt, or Argon2 for password hashing — never SHA-* for passwords</li>
  <li>Use <code>crypto.timingSafeEqual()</code> for constant-time signature comparison</li>
  <li>Store the salt alongside the hash — bcrypt encodes it in the output automatically</li>
</ul>

